<Section collapsed="true" isCollapsible="true" drawButton="true" MultipleChoiceAnswerIndex="-1" MultipleChoiceRandomizeChoices="false" TrueFalseAnswerIndex="-1" EssayAnswerRows="5" EssayAnswerColumns="60"><Title><Text-field style="Heading 1" layout="Heading 1"><Font opaque="true" background="[0,255,0]">Question 1.</Font></Text-field></Title>
<Group labelreference="L106" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Write a Maple procedure <Font italic="true">ForwardSub</Font> taking as input a matrix <Font bold="true">L</Font> and a vector  <Font bold="true">y</Font> and returning the solution to <Font bold="true">Lx </Font>= <Font bold="true">y</Font> constructed using forward substitution. Your procedure should return a message if either <Font bold="true">L</Font> or <Font bold="true">y</Font> are not of the right dimensions or if <Font bold="true">L</Font> is not invertible. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">
First load in the backsub as an example (and for question 3):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Section collapsed="true" isCollapsible="true" drawButton="true" MultipleChoiceAnswerIndex="-1" MultipleChoiceRandomizeChoices="false" TrueFalseAnswerIndex="-1" EssayAnswerRows="5" EssayAnswerColumns="60"><Title><Text-field style="Heading 1" layout="Heading 1">BackSub code</Text-field></Title>
<Group labelreference="L107" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">BackSub := proc(U::Matrix, y::Vector)::vector;
local x, i, j, n;
if ColumnDimension(U) &lt;&gt; RowDimension(U) or ColumnDimension(U) &lt;&gt; Dimension(y) or
RowDimension(U) &lt;&gt; Dimension(y) then return &quot;Dimensions not right&quot;; end if;
for i to Dimension(y) do
if U[i, i] = 0 then return &quot;Matrix is singular&quot;; end if;
end do;
x := Vector(Dimension(y));
n := Dimension(y);
for i from n by -1 to 1 do x[i] := (y[i] - (U . x)[i])/U[i, i];
end do;
return x;
end proc:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
</Section>
<Group labelreference="L108" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">We fix this code to create ForwardSub below:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Section collapsed="true" isCollapsible="true" drawButton="true" MultipleChoiceAnswerIndex="-1" MultipleChoiceRandomizeChoices="false" TrueFalseAnswerIndex="-1" EssayAnswerRows="5" EssayAnswerColumns="60"><Title><Text-field style="Heading 1" layout="Heading 1">ForwardSub code</Text-field></Title>
<Group labelreference="L109" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">ForwardSub:=proc(L::Matrix,y::Vector)::Vector;
local DL, RL, CL, Ry, Cy, x, n, i;
DL := Determinant(L);
RL := RowDimension(L);
CL := ColumnDimension(L);
Ry := RowDimension(y);
Cy := ColumnDimension(y);
n := Dimension(y);
x := Vector(Dimension(y));
if DL=0 then printf(&quot;Error: Matrix input must be invertible&quot;); 
elif Cy&gt;1 then printf(&quot;Error: Vector input has incorrect dimensions&quot;); 
elif RL&lt;&gt;CL then printf(&quot;Error: Matrix input must be a square matrix&quot;);
elif Ry&lt;&gt;Ry then printf(&quot;Error: Input Matrix / Vector must be of equal dimension&quot;);
else for i from 1 to n do x[i] := (y[i] - (L . x)[i])/L[i, i];
end do;
end if;
return x;
end proc:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
</Section>
<Section collapsed="true" isCollapsible="true" drawButton="true" MultipleChoiceAnswerIndex="-1" MultipleChoiceRandomizeChoices="false" TrueFalseAnswerIndex="-1" EssayAnswerRows="5" EssayAnswerColumns="60"><Title><Text-field style="Heading 2" layout="Heading 2">How does it work?</Text-field></Title>
<Group labelreference="L168" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">The code takes the Determinant, Row Dimension, Column Dimension of the Matrix <Font bold="true">L</Font> and saves them as DL, RL and CL respectively.
</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">It takes the Column Dimension and Row Dimension and Dimension (Which is equal to the Row Dimension) of the</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">It creates a new vector &quot;<Font bold="true">x</Font>&quot; and sets it to have the same Dimension as the vector <Font bold="true">y</Font>.
</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">If the determinant of the matrix <Font bold="true">M</Font> is 0 then the code returns the error message &quot;Error: Matrix input must be invertible&quot; and terminates.
</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">If the Column Dimension of <Font bold="true">y </Font>is greater than 1 (meaning you've input a matrix or row vector) then the code returns the error message &quot;Vector input has incorrect dimensions&quot; and terminates.
</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">If the Row Dimension of the matrix <Font bold="true">M </Font>is not equal to the Column Dimension then the code returns the error message &quot;Matrix input must be a square matrix&quot; and terminates.
</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">If the Row Dimension of the vector <Font bold="true">y </Font>is not equal to the Row Dimension of the matrix <Font bold="true">M </Font>then the code returns the error message &quot;Input Matrix / Vector must be of equal dimension&quot; and terminates.
</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">If the input matrix and vector are acceptable then code begins the forward substitution and individually replaces each value in the vector <Font bold="true">x</Font> with a rearrangement the corresponding <Font bold="true">y</Font>-value minus corresponding value of the dot product of the matrix <Font bold="true">L </Font>and the vector <Font bold="true">x </Font>all divided by the corresponding diagonal entry of <Font bold="true">L</Font>.
</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" initial="-1" bulletsuffix="." bullet="numeric">Once it has passed through each entry for the vector <Font bold="true">x</Font>, the code returns the final vector <Font bold="true">x </Font>and terminates.</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
</Section>
